<h2 class="title">The Early Days</h2>
<p class="description">Our father grew up in Hong Kong and was the third of 6 sons. Our grandfather owned a small business selling Chinese antiques, which coincidentally was named P.C. Lu &amp; Sons. And while he started his business from nothing, he was able to make enough money to send my father to one semester of college. Luckily, business took off after our dad went to college, and he was able to graduate from M.I.T. with a Ph.D. in astrophysics.</p>
